<body>

<h1>@HI{{soudesu}} (appearance, looks like)</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<p>
<dl>
<li> @FORMATION{{@Vmasustem{{}}@HI{{@EM{{soudesu}}}}}}
<li> @FORMATION{{@Aistem{{}}@HI{{@EM{{soudesu}}}}}}
<li> @FORMATION{{@Anastem{{}}@HI{{@EM{{soudesu}}}}}}
<li> @FORMATION{{@Vmasustem{{}}@HI{{@EM{{soumonai}}}}}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="occurrence">When</a> the present state of something leads the speaker to presuppose an occurrence, the speaker uses this sentence
pattern with a verb to state it. The speaker is expressing a conjecture based on visual information and so this pattern
is only used when the speaker directly observes something. Furthermore, the conjecture concerns the future
state and so this sentence patten cannot refer to conjecture about a past state.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{now}}nimo@KJ{{rain}}ga@KJ{{descend}}ri@EM{{soudesu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    It lools like it will rain at any moment.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{kono@KJ{{fee^logic}}ha@KJ{{spicy}}@EM{{soudesu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    This dish looks spicy.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{kono@KJ{{desk}}ha@KJ{{length^husband}}@EM{{soudesu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    This desk looks strong and durable.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{ii}} becomes @HI{{yosasoudesu}} in this sentence pattern.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{he^woman}}ha@KJ{{head}}gayosa@EM{{soudesu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    She seems to be bright.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="nai">In</a> the negative form, @HI{{nai}} becomes @HI{{@EM{{nasasou}}}}.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{ano@KJ{{reflect^brush-stroke}}haamariomoshirokunasasoudesune.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    That film doesn't look very interesting does it?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="appearance">When</a> this pattern is used with an adjective, it means that something appears to be that adjective.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{kono@KT{{ke-ki}}haoishi@EM{{sou}}desune.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    This cake looks yummy.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="pre-nominal">When</a> used as a noun modifier, the expression becomes @HI{{@EM{{souna}}}}.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{oishi@EM{{souna}}@KT{{ke-ki}}gaarimasune.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    There's a delicious looking cake, isn't there?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="adverb">When</a> used as an adverb, the expression becomes @HI{{@EM{{souni}}}}.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{child}}domotachiga@FG{{@KJ{{music}}:tano}}shi@EM{{souni}}@FG{{@KJ{{play}}:aso}}ndeimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    The children seem to be playing happily.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="soumonai">The</a> prediction that an event will probably not occur is expressed using @Vmasustem{{}}@HI{{@EM{{soumonai}}}}.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{kono@KJ{{rain}}hamadayami@EM{{soumonai}}desune.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    This rain doesn't look like stopping yet does it?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRNDEND{{}}

